764
00:37:51,751 --> 00:37:53,792
It's time to put it
on the table.

765
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:57,959
So you've changed your mind
about the five thousand dollars?

766
00:37:57,959 --> 00:37:59,250
Look how about this
for a new deal?

767
00:37:59,250 --> 00:38:02,292
I get out of here, and you keep
the five grand. Okay? See ya.

768
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,250
There is no new deal.

769
00:38:05,250 --> 00:38:10,125
You leave here with
the 5000 dollars
when I say.

770
00:38:10,125 --> 00:38:14,042
And I won't be saying
anything until my father
says that I can marry Bruce.

771
00:38:14,042 --> 00:38:15,042
Is that clear?

772
00:38:15,042 --> 00:38:16,042
Forget it.

773
00:38:23,042 --> 00:38:25,209
All right, I'll double it.

774
00:38:25,209 --> 00:38:26,667
Another five thousand.

775
00:38:30,918 --> 00:38:32,250
Another five?

776
00:38:37,209 --> 00:38:39,042
May I come in?

777
00:38:40,334 --> 00:38:42,751
Carlos, I want to apologize.

778
00:38:42,751 --> 00:38:45,876
My brother-in-law
can be very insensitive.

779
00:38:45,876 --> 00:38:48,042
He's Australian, you see.

780
00:38:48,042 --> 00:38:51,125
When I told him that you and
Alexandra were getting married,

781
00:38:51,125 --> 00:38:52,375
I said if he didn't like you

782
00:38:52,375 --> 00:38:54,959
he needn't bother attending
any more family functions.

783
00:38:54,959 --> 00:38:58,042
Uh, you mean you're
gonna let me marry her?

784
00:38:58,042 --> 00:39:00,709
You're gonna let
me marry him?

785
00:39:00,709 --> 00:39:03,542
Well, it's a little too
rapid for my taste sweetheart.

786
00:39:03,542 --> 00:39:07,042
But... a deal's a deal.

787
00:39:07,042 --> 00:39:10,334
Welcome to the family.

788
00:39:10,334 --> 00:39:11,959
Son.

789
00:39:16,542 --> 00:39:17,918
Goodnight.

790
00:39:20,083 --> 00:39:22,042
Goodnight, sweetheart.

791
00:39:37,626 --> 00:39:39,751
Shut up. This isn't funny.

792
00:39:43,459 --> 00:39:44,792
What?

793
00:39:44,792 --> 00:39:46,959
Hey, what about a June
wedding, honey?

794
00:39:46,959 --> 00:39:49,209
I like June. You know,
not too hot, not too cold.

795
00:39:49,209 --> 00:39:51,167
What do you think,
sweetheart, June?

796
00:39:51,959 --> 00:39:53,751
I said shut up and get out.

797
00:39:55,959 --> 00:39:57,042
Get out!

798
00:39:57,042 --> 00:39:58,667
Oh, get out. OK.

799
00:39:58,667 --> 00:40:01,459
Get out!

800
00:40:01,459 --> 00:40:05,042
OK, OK. [hums wedding march]
Dun dun da dun.

801
00:40:05,042 --> 00:40:10,042
Dun Dun da Dun.
And 10,000 dollars to boot.

802
00:40:10,042 --> 00:40:12,042
Da dun dun da dun.

803
00:40:15,959 --> 00:40:18,042
[horse neighs]

804
00:40:25,250 --> 00:40:28,250
[Carlos humming
wedding march]

805
00:40:28,250 --> 00:40:29,792
Oh, Carlos.

806
00:40:29,792 --> 00:40:30,459
Huh?

807
00:40:30,459 --> 00:40:32,959
- Oh, hi.
- Entrez.

808
00:40:36,792 --> 00:40:39,042
- How you doin?
- Sit down.

809
00:40:39,042 --> 00:40:40,417
Sit down.

810
00:40:46,334 --> 00:40:47,542
Well, did you
have a good time?

811
00:40:47,542 --> 00:40:50,959
Would you mind brushing
the back of my hair?

812
00:40:50,959 --> 00:40:52,501
I can't seem to reach it.

813
00:40:52,501 --> 00:40:54,250
Oh, yeah sure.

814
00:40:54,250 --> 00:40:56,042
Thank you.

815
00:41:00,042 --> 00:41:01,501
- [snorting]
- Oh. I'm sorry.
Did I hurt you?

816
00:41:01,501 --> 00:41:04,459
No no. Don't stop.
You won't hurt me.

817
00:41:08,209 --> 00:41:11,751
[snorting and blowing
like a horse] Harder.

818
00:41:11,751 --> 00:41:13,542
Harder?

819
00:41:13,542 --> 00:41:14,834
- [blows] Harder.
- Harder?

820
00:41:14,834 --> 00:41:16,042
Harder!

821
00:41:16,042 --> 00:41:19,709
[whinnies] Faster, faster.

822
00:41:22,626 --> 00:41:26,042
Harder, faster.

823
00:41:29,584 --> 00:41:32,000
- Say something
in Mexican.
- What?

824
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,083
Say something in Mexican.

825
00:41:34,042 --> 00:41:35,626
Quick.

826
00:41:35,626 --> 00:41:37,167
La chica es loca.

827
00:41:42,834 --> 00:41:46,042
- [neighs blows and whinnies]
- Is there a horse the house?

828
00:41:52,667 --> 00:41:54,042
- [snorting]
- If I take my hand off

829
00:41:54,042 --> 00:41:56,667
will you be quiet?

830
00:41:56,667 --> 00:41:58,501
You sure?

831
00:42:03,709 --> 00:42:05,584
I'm sorry.

832
00:42:05,584 --> 00:42:08,083
I don't know what
came over me.

833
00:42:08,083 --> 00:42:11,083
You scared the
hell out of me.

834
00:42:11,083 --> 00:42:12,667
Aye caramba!

835
00:42:12,667 --> 00:42:15,250
[shrieks] Yeah!
Viva Zapata!

836
00:42:18,042 --> 00:42:19,042
Hey, relax!

837
00:42:21,083 --> 00:42:22,417
Calm down.

838
00:42:26,042 --> 00:42:27,042
I'm Mexi...

839
00:42:27,042 --> 00:42:28,751
I mean, I'm not Mexican.

840
00:42:28,751 --> 00:42:30,292
Oh, look, a kangaroo.

841
00:42:32,709 --> 00:42:35,375
- [making loud snorting noises]
- We can talk about this.

842
00:42:35,375 --> 00:42:36,751
Let's make a deal.

843
00:42:37,959 --> 00:42:40,042
No. no!

844
00:42:40,292 --> 00:42:41,834
Oh, dear.

845
00:42:41,834 --> 00:42:44,209
Maggie's having those
horse nightmares again.

846
00:42:51,125 --> 00:42:53,584
[Maggie squealing and snorting]

847
00:43:00,751 --> 00:43:03,042
Jump my little jumping bean.

848
00:43:21,042 --> 00:43:23,459
Eh.

849
00:43:25,083 --> 00:43:27,792
Whoa, what a ride!

850
00:43:27,792 --> 00:43:29,375
All right babe,
you're next.

851
00:43:29,375 --> 00:43:30,792
I'm oiled up.

852
00:43:31,459 --> 00:43:34,834
My! What a
strange young man.

853
00:43:34,834 --> 00:43:36,375
Not for this family.

854
00:43:36,792 --> 00:43:38,042
[whimpers]

855
00:43:48,751 --> 00:43:50,209
[Carlos singing]

856
00:43:50,209 --> 00:43:52,584
Hey, top of the
morning, Jeeves.

857
00:43:52,584 --> 00:43:53,542
Hey, good morning,
everybody.

858
00:43:53,542 --> 00:43:55,042
Hey, babe.

859
00:43:55,042 --> 00:43:56,542
I'm surprised you're up.

860
00:43:56,542 --> 00:43:58,042
I'm surprised
you could walk.

861
00:43:59,375 --> 00:44:00,792
I managed.

862
00:44:00,792 --> 00:44:04,083
Tell me have you two
settled on a date yet?

863
00:44:04,083 --> 00:44:05,501
We'll let you know.

864
00:44:05,501 --> 00:44:08,584
You could give us a hint,
couldn't you Alexandra?

865
00:44:08,584 --> 00:44:10,751
I'm usually free
in the afternoons.

866
00:44:12,209 --> 00:44:15,375
You know, Carlos, I'd be
delighted to take you
into the business.

867
00:44:15,375 --> 00:44:16,292
Who me?

868
00:44:16,292 --> 00:44:19,042
Nah, I'm not into
business, man.

869
00:44:19,042 --> 00:44:20,834
Well, you're quick.
You're good with people.

870
00:44:20,834 --> 00:44:23,042
I think you'd be great.
Don't you darling?

871
00:44:24,042 --> 00:44:25,667
Nah, I don't think so.

872
00:44:25,667 --> 00:44:28,042
Hey, tell you what.
You know who'd be
great at business?

873
00:44:28,042 --> 00:44:30,125
Your daughter, man.
She drives a mean bargain.

874
00:44:30,125 --> 00:44:32,083
Mm, I've been telling
her for years.

875
00:44:33,709 --> 00:44:36,375
Do you think you could
talk some sense into her?

876
00:44:36,375 --> 00:44:38,000
Who me?

877
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:39,626
Yeah. No problem.

878
00:44:41,375 --> 00:44:42,626
[sniffs]

879
00:44:44,959 --> 00:44:46,042
Pew.

880
00:44:47,125 --> 00:44:49,584
Well, if we're going to
beat the Sunday traffic,

881
00:44:49,584 --> 00:44:51,459
better hit the road.

882
00:44:51,459 --> 00:44:53,876
Hmm?
Oh...

883
00:44:55,292 --> 00:44:58,042
Well, it's been
a slice.

884
00:44:58,042 --> 00:44:58,959
Uh, leave them.

885
00:44:58,959 --> 00:45:00,501
Edison will
take care of it.

886
00:45:00,501 --> 00:45:02,459
Where I come from everybody
does their own dishes,

887
00:45:02,459 --> 00:45:03,417
you know what I mean?

888
00:45:03,417 --> 00:45:06,042
Travel broadens the
horizons. Leave it.

889
00:45:06,042 --> 00:45:08,083
It'll just take five minutes.

890
00:45:08,083 --> 00:45:11,083
I said leave them.

891
00:45:16,083 --> 00:45:18,417
Well, see you
in the Spring,

892
00:45:18,417 --> 00:45:20,751
if we don't see
you in the mattress.

893
00:45:20,751 --> 00:45:22,167
Later on.

894
00:45:22,167 --> 00:45:23,918
Cheerio, Jeeves.

895
00:45:37,626 --> 00:45:39,876
Incredible performance.

896
00:45:39,876 --> 00:45:42,626
I wonder what she'll
come up with for act three.

897
00:45:42,626 --> 00:45:47,083
She must really be in love to
put up with all this nonsense.

898
00:45:47,083 --> 00:45:49,751
Perhaps we should just
let her marry him.

899
00:45:49,751 --> 00:45:52,709
Likeable fellow,
this Carlos.

900
00:45:52,709 --> 00:45:55,501
I meant Bruce,
not Carlos.

901
00:45:56,959 --> 00:45:59,250
Let's just play along
a bit longer.

902
00:46:05,292 --> 00:46:07,918
Hey listen, uh, I don't
really have a bank account.

903
00:46:07,918 --> 00:46:09,834
You think I can get
the money in cash?

904
00:46:09,834 --> 00:46:11,083
What money?

905
00:46:11,083 --> 00:46:12,083
What do you mean,
what money?

906
00:46:12,083 --> 00:46:13,209
The ten grand.

907
00:46:13,209 --> 00:46:14,375
Are you kidding?

908
00:46:14,375 --> 00:46:17,083
Oh, come on. You're
not gonna stiff me are ya?

909
00:46:17,083 --> 00:46:19,083
You said you didn't
want the money.

910
00:46:19,083 --> 00:46:21,209
'Cause I wanted to quit,
but you made me stay.

911
00:46:21,209 --> 00:46:23,083
Dear God, don't you
understand anything?

912
00:46:23,083 --> 00:46:25,584
I wanted you to stay
so father would hate you.

913
00:46:25,584 --> 00:46:29,375
Instead you sit around like old
mates, talking about my career.

914
00:46:29,375 --> 00:46:32,626
Hey, I did everything
I could to make him
think I was a jerk.

915
00:46:32,626 --> 00:46:34,751
And look what happened,
he loves you.

916
00:46:34,751 --> 00:46:36,125
It's not my fault.

917
00:46:36,125 --> 00:46:37,834
He's only human.

918
00:46:37,834 --> 00:46:39,250
Put it this way.

919
00:46:39,250 --> 00:46:41,751
I go to your restaurant
and order a meal.

920
00:46:41,751 --> 00:46:43,918
You go to the kitchen, but you
come back without the food.

921
00:46:43,918 --> 00:46:45,292
Do you still think I should pay?

922
00:46:45,292 --> 00:46:47,584
What the hell
does that mean?

923
00:46:56,292 --> 00:46:57,459
Hey, where are we goin'?

924
00:46:57,459 --> 00:46:59,042
We're going through Walingatta.

925
00:46:59,042 --> 00:47:02,501
I want to surprise Bruce at the
hotel. We'll stay the night.

926
00:47:02,501 --> 00:47:04,459
Stay the night?

927
00:47:04,459 --> 00:47:05,667
If you don't want to sleep over,

928
00:47:05,667 --> 00:47:09,083
you can get the bus
back to Sydney.

929
00:47:09,083 --> 00:47:11,083
Yeah, cool whatever.

930
00:47:24,083 --> 00:47:26,125
Hey, they could use some help.
Why didn't you stop?

931
00:47:26,125 --> 00:47:27,959
It's a trick.

932
00:47:27,959 --> 00:47:29,751
What are you talking about?

933
00:47:29,751 --> 00:47:33,083
They get you to stop
and then they rob you blind.

934
00:47:34,125 --> 00:47:36,709
I can't believe you.

935
00:47:36,709 --> 00:47:39,417
Hey, you'd stop if it
was a Rolls wouldn't you?

936
00:47:39,417 --> 00:47:41,417
Or maybe a Mercedes
or a Jaguar?

937
00:47:41,417 --> 00:47:44,209
Alright. You've made
your point.

938
00:48:01,125 --> 00:48:02,667
Hey, dude.

939
00:48:03,834 --> 00:48:04,792
G'day, mate.

940
00:48:04,792 --> 00:48:06,375
- How ya doin'?
- You got any water?

941
00:48:07,792 --> 00:48:08,918
Yeah, here's some.

942
00:48:08,918 --> 00:48:11,083
Go ahead.
Have at it.

943
00:48:20,167 --> 00:48:22,083
I'm gonna give'em a hand.

944
00:48:24,542 --> 00:48:26,918
Don't tell me, let me guess.
A flat tire?

945
00:48:26,918 --> 00:48:28,083
You're right.

946
00:48:28,083 --> 00:48:29,876
I was going to take the
spare in and get it fixed,

947
00:48:29,876 --> 00:48:33,083
but I didn't have the cash,
so I took a chance.

948
00:48:33,083 --> 00:48:34,792
Bad luck, huh.

949
00:48:34,792 --> 00:48:36,459
Well, what can
we do for ya?

950
00:48:36,459 --> 00:48:37,876
Don't know.

951
00:48:37,876 --> 00:48:40,042
can't all fit in the
back of your car.

952
00:48:40,042 --> 00:48:42,083
That'd be a little crowded.

953
00:48:42,083 --> 00:48:43,501
Uh, hm.

954
00:48:43,501 --> 00:48:46,042
Tell you what.
Give me a hand.

955
00:48:46,042 --> 00:48:47,542
Let's have a look.

956
00:48:47,542 --> 00:48:49,375
I'll just throw
this on the ground.

957
00:48:55,083 --> 00:48:56,292
What do you think?

958
00:48:56,292 --> 00:48:57,209
Yeah?

959
00:48:57,209 --> 00:48:58,125
Hope it's enough
to rock and roll.

960
00:48:58,125 --> 00:49:01,083
- She's a beauty.
- Yeah.

961
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,083
Uh, hello.
It's my tire.

962
00:49:04,083 --> 00:49:06,083
Oh, don't worry.
You'll get it back.

963
00:49:09,125 --> 00:49:11,834
I have somewhere to go.

964
00:49:11,834 --> 00:49:13,083
Hey, good idea.

965
00:49:13,083 --> 00:49:15,083
Why don't you go down
there and take a walk?

966
00:49:15,083 --> 00:49:16,042
What a beautiful day.

967
00:49:16,042 --> 00:49:18,876
Yeah, take a nice
long walk. Okay?

968
00:49:18,876 --> 00:49:20,459
Eh, nature.

969
00:49:20,459 --> 00:49:22,083
I'll be right with ya.

970
00:49:25,083 --> 00:49:26,334
Where you come from, mate?

971
00:49:26,334 --> 00:49:28,250
Me? Uh, L.A.

972
00:49:28,250 --> 00:49:29,334
How about you?

973
00:49:29,334 --> 00:49:32,584
Whyalla. What are you
doing over here?

974
00:49:32,584 --> 00:49:35,125
Oh, well it wasn't
working out in L.A.

975
00:49:35,125 --> 00:49:37,542
so I thought I'd give
this place a try you know?

976
00:49:37,542 --> 00:49:39,125
What made you
pick Australia?

977
00:49:41,459 --> 00:49:44,542
Tell you the truth I
kept seeing this guy on TV.

978
00:49:44,542 --> 00:49:46,751
He was saying "G'day, mate."

979
00:49:46,751 --> 00:49:48,542
Throw another
shrimp on the barbie.

980
00:49:48,542 --> 00:49:50,083
Sitting there drinking a
beer... beautiful beach.

981
00:49:50,083 --> 00:49:52,626
I thought hey,
could be worse.

982
00:49:54,083 --> 00:49:57,501
Lately I've been thinking
that I'm the shrimp on
the barbie though.

983
00:49:57,501 --> 00:50:00,709
It looks like you've
done alright for
yourself so far mate.

984
00:50:02,584 --> 00:50:05,667
Isn't that right honey,
could be worse?
What do you think?

985
00:50:05,667 --> 00:50:07,459
Having a good time, huh?

986
00:50:07,459 --> 00:50:09,083
How 'bout we get some
land over here, huh?

987
00:50:09,083 --> 00:50:11,083
Maybe we raise some
kids, some sheep.

988
00:50:11,083 --> 00:50:13,083
Put a little house up
there. What do you think?

989
00:50:13,083 --> 00:50:17,083
You two remind me of me
and the missus when we
was first hitched.

990
00:50:17,083 --> 00:50:18,542
Bloody lovebirds we was.

991
00:50:18,542 --> 00:50:20,834
Couldn't keep our eyes
off each other.

992
00:50:20,834 --> 00:50:23,083
I know what you mean.

993
00:50:23,083 --> 00:50:27,751
Thank you pretty lady.

994
00:50:27,751 --> 00:50:30,626
Combination wedding gift
and good luck charm.

995
00:50:30,626 --> 00:50:32,834
Wear it in good health.

996
00:50:32,834 --> 00:50:37,083
Oh, that's really
beautiful, huh?

997
00:50:37,083 --> 00:50:38,501
Say "thank you" now.

998
00:50:40,709 --> 00:50:42,042
Thank you.

999
00:50:56,584 --> 00:50:59,083
We're gonna have to make
up the time you wasted playing

1000
00:50:59,083 --> 00:51:01,083
Santa Claus with those people.

1001
00:51:01,083 --> 00:51:03,209
I can't believe you
gave my tire away.

1002
00:51:03,209 --> 00:51:04,792
Do you know how
much that's worth?

1003
00:51:04,792 --> 00:51:08,000
What are you talking about,
gave it away? I didn't
give it away.

1004
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:09,083
He was gonna bring it back.

1005
00:51:09,083 --> 00:51:11,959
You just wouldn't give
him your address.

1006
00:51:11,959 --> 00:51:14,125
Hey, besides, he gave
you that beautiful crystal.

1007
00:51:15,334 --> 00:51:17,292
This piece of junk.

1008
00:51:21,667 --> 00:51:24,417
At least I only lose a
100 dollar tire this way.

1009
00:51:24,417 --> 00:51:26,083
Say what?

1010
00:51:26,083 --> 00:51:27,792
If I gave them my address,

1011
00:51:27,792 --> 00:51:30,959
I'd come home tomorrow
to an empty apartment.

1012
00:51:30,959 --> 00:51:33,584
Oh come on,
that guy was OK.

1013
00:51:33,584 --> 00:51:35,125
You gotta
trust somebody.

1014
00:51:35,125 --> 00:51:38,501
It's easy to trust people when
you don't have anything to lose.

1015
00:51:38,501 --> 00:51:41,292
Hey, who died and made
you Darth Vader, huh?

1016
00:51:42,250 --> 00:51:44,042
[loud pop]

1017
00:51:44,918 --> 00:51:46,751
