01:09:23,167 --> 01:09:24,292
Allez, allez,Alex.
Don't forget Bruce's party.

1270
01:09:24,292 --> 01:09:26,667
...don't forget,
it pays to be nice.

1271
01:09:26,667 --> 01:09:28,042
Over to you, Tony.

1272
01:09:30,792 --> 01:09:33,209
Alex, what's the matter?
What's wrong?

1273
01:09:47,375 --> 01:09:48,918
That'll be all, gentlemen.

1274
01:09:57,292 --> 01:09:59,792
Your father's
right in here, Miss.

1275
01:09:59,792 --> 01:10:01,042
Thanks.

1276
01:10:01,042 --> 01:10:02,542
Well, Alexandra.

1277
01:10:02,542 --> 01:10:05,250
And to what do I owe the
pleasure of this
unexpected visit?

1278
01:10:05,250 --> 01:10:06,751
Well, I was just
in the neighborhood

1279
01:10:06,751 --> 01:10:10,209
and I thought I would
stop by and see
how you were doing.

1280
01:10:11,584 --> 01:10:13,209
Very thoughtful.

1281
01:10:14,876 --> 01:10:16,417
So, how are you doing?

1282
01:10:16,417 --> 01:10:17,375
Never better.

1283
01:10:17,375 --> 01:10:18,918
And you?

1284
01:10:19,918 --> 01:10:21,501
I'm great.

1285
01:10:21,501 --> 01:10:23,209
Everything is great.

1286
01:10:24,209 --> 01:10:25,209
That bad, eh?

1287
01:10:25,209 --> 01:10:27,584
No, it's fine.
Really.

1288
01:10:28,751 --> 01:10:30,083
How's Carlos?

1289
01:10:31,584 --> 01:10:33,459
Carlos...

1290
01:10:33,459 --> 01:10:36,918
As a matter of fact,
that didn't work out.

1291
01:10:36,918 --> 01:10:39,042
Pity. Nice chap.

1292
01:10:39,042 --> 01:10:41,626
Your mother will be
disappointed.

1293
01:10:41,626 --> 01:10:44,626
Are you 100 percent set on
marrying this Bruce character?

1294
01:10:44,626 --> 01:10:46,501
Yes, I am.

1295
01:10:46,501 --> 01:10:47,876
Then what's wrong?

1296
01:10:47,876 --> 01:10:49,250
Nothing.

1297
01:10:51,083 --> 01:10:52,125
Now you're set on marrying him,

1298
01:10:52,125 --> 01:10:54,042
you're having
second thoughts, aren't you?

1299
01:10:54,042 --> 01:10:56,250
No, not at all.

1300
01:10:56,250 --> 01:10:57,375
Well...

1301
01:10:59,083 --> 01:11:02,000
You know how I feel about him.

1302
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:07,584
And as your father Alexandra,
just your plain, old dad,

1303
01:11:07,584 --> 01:11:10,667
if you ever want to change
your mind, it's not too late.

1304
01:11:22,209 --> 01:11:26,959
I haven't seen you cry like this
since you were a little girl.

1305
01:11:26,959 --> 01:11:30,751
It's just everything
all at once.

1306
01:11:46,125 --> 01:11:50,167
I've been like a kid.
Like a rebellious teenager.

1307
01:11:51,709 --> 01:11:54,292
I just wanted to beat
you at something, you know?

1308
01:11:54,292 --> 01:11:58,626
Make you say yes,
when I knew you'd say, no.

1309
01:12:01,000 --> 01:12:03,209
I'm sorry.

1310
01:12:03,209 --> 01:12:07,751
I had no idea things were
so bad between you and me.

1311
01:12:07,751 --> 01:12:11,792
I'm really very
sorry about that.

1312
01:12:16,626 --> 01:12:20,209
I don't remember the last time
you said, "I'm sorry."

1313
01:12:20,209 --> 01:12:23,125
I don't remember
the last time I was wrong.

1314
01:12:31,542 --> 01:12:34,709
I don't think I want to spend
the rest of my life with Bruce.

1315
01:12:35,501 --> 01:12:37,709
Would you like me
to talk to him?

1316
01:12:37,709 --> 01:12:40,209
Let him down gently.

1317
01:12:42,501 --> 01:12:46,459
No, this time I'm
going to clean up my own mess.

1318
01:12:49,334 --> 01:12:52,209
I'm throwing him
a surprise party tonight

1319
01:12:52,209 --> 01:12:55,334
but afterwards...

1320
01:13:03,459 --> 01:13:05,042
You're a love.

1321
01:13:07,250 --> 01:13:11,250
Oh, Alex, just a second.

1322
01:13:12,334 --> 01:13:13,876
Collins, still out there?

1323
01:13:13,876 --> 01:13:14,834
Yes, Sir Ian.

1324
01:13:14,834 --> 01:13:16,125
Have him bring
that envelope please.

1325
01:13:16,125 --> 01:13:17,334
Thank you.

1326
01:13:17,334 --> 01:13:21,209
Mr. Collins is a photographer.
He took some snapshots for me.

1327
01:13:21,209 --> 01:13:24,083
Thank you, Collins. You'll be
quite interested in these, dear.

1328
01:13:24,083 --> 01:13:25,250
What are they?

1329
01:13:25,250 --> 01:13:26,501
Fish.

1330
01:13:26,501 --> 01:13:28,626
Fish?

1331
01:13:28,626 --> 01:13:31,375
Most unusual fish.

1332
01:13:37,250 --> 01:13:39,292
[all] Surprise.

1333
01:13:41,709 --> 01:13:44,250
You little devil.
You remembered.

1334
01:13:44,250 --> 01:13:46,667
Oh, you haven't seen
anything yet.

1335
01:13:48,083 --> 01:13:49,250
Happy Birthday.

1336
01:13:49,250 --> 01:13:52,334
[party chatter]

1337
01:13:56,292 --> 01:13:58,709
Ok, attention everyone.

1338
01:13:58,709 --> 01:14:01,250
We have a special event.

1339
01:14:01,250 --> 01:14:04,250
Everyone find a seat on the
floor, doesn't matter where.

1340
01:14:04,250 --> 01:14:09,042
And Bruce, darling.
Right here. Place of honor.

1341
01:14:11,375 --> 01:14:13,584
Drink for you.

1342
01:14:13,584 --> 01:14:16,083
You know, I was thinking.

1343
01:14:16,083 --> 01:14:19,250
What does one give to a man
who has everything?

1344
01:14:19,250 --> 01:14:20,626
[man] A shot of penicillin?

1345
01:14:20,626 --> 01:14:21,959
[all laugh]

1346
01:14:21,959 --> 01:14:23,751
[man] Good one.

1347
01:14:23,751 --> 01:14:28,375
So, I've prepared a little
history of our time together.

1348
01:14:29,542 --> 01:14:32,250
Dominique, would you
get the lights please?

1349
01:14:37,250 --> 01:14:40,083
Gstaad, where we first met.

1350
01:14:42,042 --> 01:14:44,250
[Alex] Love at first sight.

1351
01:14:44,250 --> 01:14:46,250
Our first date.

1352
01:14:48,250 --> 01:14:51,709
Bruce, always the salesman.

1353
01:14:51,709 --> 01:14:53,417
Four X would be proud.

1354
01:14:58,250 --> 01:15:00,375
[man] Uh oh, busted.

1355
01:15:04,751 --> 01:15:08,292
A real man's man.

1356
01:15:16,042 --> 01:15:20,083
I don't know where this is,
must have been another holiday.

1357
01:15:21,375 --> 01:15:22,751
Where is this?

1358
01:15:22,751 --> 01:15:24,709
Dominique, I don't remember when
you came on holiday with us.

1359
01:15:24,709 --> 01:15:25,918
When was that?

1360
01:15:31,167 --> 01:15:33,375
Where is this?

1361
01:15:33,375 --> 01:15:36,375
I don't even
remember being there.

1362
01:15:54,709 --> 01:15:56,250
What's this?

1363
01:15:56,250 --> 01:16:01,250
This is my best friend
and my fiancée.

1364
01:16:01,250 --> 01:16:05,667
And she's leaving his room,
putting her clothes on.

1365
01:16:05,667 --> 01:16:07,918
I'm shocked.

1366
01:16:11,918 --> 01:16:14,584
And, how did
Carlos get here?

1367
01:16:20,250 --> 01:16:24,792
Ooh. Carlos must have made
Bruce very mad.

1368
01:16:24,792 --> 01:16:26,250
Darling, let me explain...

1369
01:16:26,250 --> 01:16:29,334
There's no need to explain.

1370
01:16:29,334 --> 01:16:32,250
A picture is worth
a thousand words.

1371
01:16:35,918 --> 01:16:38,250
I think we've seen enough.

1372
01:16:38,250 --> 01:16:39,375
Lights.

1373
01:16:42,042 --> 01:16:44,834
Dominique, leaving so soon?

1374
01:16:44,834 --> 01:16:47,000
You haven't even had any
cake yet.

1375
01:16:50,375 --> 01:16:52,250
Good, isn't it?

1376
01:16:52,250 --> 01:16:54,459
Alex, possum, let me explain.

1377
01:16:56,959 --> 01:16:59,542
That's for Carlos.

1378
01:16:59,542 --> 01:17:01,667
Well, goodnight everyone.

1379
01:17:01,667 --> 01:17:04,667
I had a wonderful time.

1380
01:17:10,751 --> 01:17:14,000
Sydney to Los Angeles, one-way?

1381
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,083
Yeah.

1382
01:17:41,918 --> 01:17:43,584
[angry crowd noise]

1383
01:17:43,584 --> 01:17:46,250
Me bladder's killing me.
I need to take a leak.

1384
01:17:48,959 --> 01:17:50,584
Where do we get the free beer?

1385
01:17:52,292 --> 01:17:53,876
It's been a nightmare.

1386
01:17:53,876 --> 01:17:55,250
Ever since that news clip
came on,

1387
01:17:55,250 --> 01:17:57,250
I've been mobbed by freeloaders.

1388
01:17:57,250 --> 01:17:58,250
We're worse off than before.

1389
01:17:58,250 --> 01:17:59,667
Oh, Carlos!

1390
01:17:59,667 --> 01:18:02,250
Where is he?
Where is he?

1391
01:18:02,250 --> 01:18:05,626
Vanished into thin air
right when I needed him most.

1392
01:18:05,626 --> 01:18:07,501
Señorita, help me, please.

1393
01:18:07,501 --> 01:18:12,000
Look at this mob. All they want
is the loo and free drinks.

1394
01:18:12,000 --> 01:18:14,250
Wayne, Wayne!
It's OK.

1395
01:18:14,250 --> 01:18:15,584
We'll find him.

1396
01:18:15,584 --> 01:18:19,125
Now, where do you think
he could have gone?

1397
01:18:19,125 --> 01:18:22,250
For all I know, he's probably
half-way to Mexico by now.

1398
01:18:28,959 --> 01:18:33,334
Flight 101 leaves Sydney
airport in 40 minutes.

1399
01:18:33,334 --> 01:18:34,626
Thanks.

1400
01:18:36,334 --> 01:18:39,083
[up-tempo music]

1401
01:19:41,834 --> 01:19:43,209
Attention all passengers,

1402
01:19:43,209 --> 01:19:47,209
Flight 101 for Los Angeles
 now boarding at gate eight

1403
01:20:11,417 --> 01:20:13,709
Has flight 101 left yet?

1404
01:20:13,709 --> 01:20:15,959
That's it just
taxiing out to the runway.

1405
01:20:15,959 --> 01:20:17,417
Well, you have to stop it.

1406
01:20:17,417 --> 01:20:19,542
Sorry madam, I can't do that.

1407
01:20:20,667 --> 01:20:21,834
Sorry.

1408
01:20:56,959 --> 01:20:58,417
Hello, darling.

1409
01:21:00,792 --> 01:21:02,417
What are you doing here?

1410
01:21:02,417 --> 01:21:04,834
Same thing you are.

1411
01:21:04,834 --> 01:21:06,751
Don't want him
to leave either.

1412
01:21:06,751 --> 01:21:10,334
It's too late anyway.
Plane's already pulling away.

1413
01:21:20,959 --> 01:21:22,417
I want you to stop that plane.

1414
01:21:22,417 --> 01:21:23,959
Right, governor.

1415
01:21:27,292 --> 01:21:28,876
It's alright, Dad.

1416
01:21:28,876 --> 01:21:30,709
I guess it just
wasn't meant to be.

1417
01:21:30,709 --> 01:21:32,459
We'll see about that.

1418
01:21:38,209 --> 01:21:39,250
Quantas Airlines.

1419
01:21:39,250 --> 01:21:40,292
I want to talk to the Chairman.

1420
01:21:40,292 --> 01:21:42,292
Just a second,
 I'll connect you.

1421
01:21:42,292 --> 01:21:44,042
Mr. Adams' office.

1422
01:21:44,042 --> 01:21:45,626
I would like to speak
with Mr. Adams.

1423
01:21:45,626 --> 01:21:48,042
I'm sorry, sir.
 He's in a meeting.

1424
01:21:48,042 --> 01:21:50,209
Yes, tell him
Mr. Ian Hobart's here.

1425
01:21:51,918 --> 01:21:54,083
Sam, hi.

1426
01:21:54,083 --> 01:21:55,918
Yes.

1427
01:21:55,918 --> 01:21:57,751
We have a flight.

1428
01:21:57,751 --> 01:21:59,501
101.

1429
01:22:00,584 --> 01:22:02,459
Bring it back, could you?

1430
01:22:08,417 --> 01:22:11,292
I'm very rich.

1431
01:22:34,292 --> 01:22:36,918
The guy at the counter said
the ticket was cool.

1432
01:22:36,918 --> 01:22:39,626
He said it was
OK to go back to L.A., man.

1433
01:22:39,626 --> 01:22:41,417
I don't know what's the problem.

1434
01:22:41,417 --> 01:22:42,792
Was it the smoke detector?

1435
01:22:42,792 --> 01:22:46,292
I just opened the door and the
smoke detector went off, man.

